definition.value: Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + lipid(in) -eq- ADP + phosphate + lipid(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + sterol(in) -eq- ADP + phosphate + sterol(out).
Catalysis of the removal of 5-formyluracil bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the oxidized pyrimidine and the deoxyribose sugar.
Catalysis of the removal of 5-hydroxymethyluracil bases by cleaving the N-C1' glycosidic bond between the oxidized pyrimidine and the deoxyribose sugar.

A protein complex that forms a coat structure on vesicles involved in exocytosis of proteins from the trans-Golgi network to the cell surface -  in Saccharomyces, the complex contains Chs5p, Chs6p, and Chs6p paralogues.
A cellular membrane associated with the pre-autophagosomal structure.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a sequence of guanine residues in an RNA molecule.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with the estrogen response element (ERE), a conserved sequence found in the promoters of genes whose expression is regulated in response to estrogen.
Facilitates the displacement of one strand of an RNA-RNA duplex and its replacement with a different strand of higher complementarity.
The space enclosed by the double membrane of a cyanelle.

Catalysis of the reaction -  deoxynucleoside triphosphate + DNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + DNA(n+1) -  the synthesis of DNA from deoxyribonucleotide triphosphates in the presence of a nucleic acid template and a 3'hydroxyl group.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nucleoside triphosphate + RNA(n) -eq- diphosphate + RNA(n+1) -  the synthesis of RNA from ribonucleotide triphosphates in the presence of a nucleic acid template.
A protein complex that contains the transcription factor Ste11 and the RNA binding protein Mei2 -  involved in regulation of conjugation in fission yeast.

label.value: replication fork processing at rDNA locus

definition.value: The process in which a DNA replication fork that has stalled at the rDNA replication fork barrier (RFB) is repaired and replication is restarted.
A protein complex that acts as a nucleotide exchange factor for the GTPase Ypt6p, and is required for fusion of endosome-derived vesicles with the Golgi.
Catalysis of the reaction -  nucleoside triphosphate + aminoglycoside -eq- diphosphate + nucleotidylaminoglycoside.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + aminoglycoside -eq- CoA + N-acetylaminoglycoside.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + aminoglycoside -eq- CoA + 1-N-acetylaminoglycoside. This is acetylation of the 1-amino group of the central deoxystreptamine ring.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + aminoglycoside -eq- ADP + phosphoaminoglycoside.
Catalysis of the reaction -  squalene -eq- triterpene.
Catalysis of the reaction -  squalene -eq- tetrahymanol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  oxidosqualene -eq- marneral.
Catalysis of the reaction -  oxidosqualene + H2O -eq- arabidiol ((13R,14R,17E)-malabarica-17,21-diene-3beta,14-diol).
Catalysis of the reaction -  oxidosqualene -eq- cucurbitadienol.
A protein complex that carries out enzymatic reactions involved in the biosynthesis of polyketides, any of a diverse group of natural products synthesized via linear poly-beta-ketones.
A polyketide synthase complex that consists of several different polypeptide chains, each of which catalyzes a single reaction.
A polyketide synthase complex that consists of two identical ketosynthase polypeptides.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of an acetyl group or groups from an acetylated sterol.
The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become associated with each other during S phase.

The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate.

label.value: establishment of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become joined along the entire length of the chromosome during S phase during a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate during a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: establishment of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: The process in which the sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome become joined along the entire length of the chromosome during S phase during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: The process in which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained as chromosomes condense, attach to the spindle in a bipolar orientation, and congress to the metaphase plate during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: regulation of maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that modulates the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained.

label.value: negative regulation of maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that decreases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained.

label.value: positive regulation of maintenance of sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that increases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained.

label.value: regulation of maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that modulates the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that decreases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a meiotic cell cycle.

label.value: positive regulation of maintenance of meiotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that increases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a meiotic cell cycle.

A multiprotein ATPase complex required for the efficient dislocation of ER-lumenal degradation substrates, and their subsequent proteolysis by the proteasome. In budding yeast, this complex includes Cdc48p, Npl4p and Ufd1p proteins.

A multiprotein complex that recognizes ERAD-luminal misfolded substrates and brings them to the ubiquitination|extraction machinery. In yeast, this complex consists of Yos9p, Kar2p and Hrd3p proteins.

label.value: regulation of maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that modulates the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: negative regulation of maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that decreases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a mitotic cell cycle.

label.value: positive regulation of maintenance of mitotic sister chromatid cohesion

definition.value: Any process that increases the extent to which the association between sister chromatids of a replicated chromosome is maintained during a mitotic cell cycle.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an apolipoprotein, the protein component of a lipoprotein complex.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with apolipoprotein A-I.
Combining with apolipoprotein A-I and transmitting the signal from one side of the membrane to the other to initiate a change in cell activity.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a very-low-density lipoprotein particle, a triglyceride-rich lipoprotein particle that is typically composed of APOB100, APOE and APOCs and has a density of about 1.006 g|ml and a diameter of between 20-80 nm.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with an apolipoprotein receptor.
